\ref{var-$t$PLF}, top panel, the outcome on the tilted pseudolikelyhood, $\mathcal{L}_t$ Eq. \eqref{$t$PLF}, of the progressive decimation: from a fully connected lattice  down to an empty lattice. The figure shows the behaviour of $\mathcal{L}_t$ for three different data sizes $M$. A clear data size dependence of the maximum point of  $\mathcal{L}_t$, signalling the most likely value for decimation, is shown. For small $M$ the most likely number of  couplings is overestimated and for increasing $M$ it tends to the true value, as displayed in Fig. \ref{PLF_peak_statistics}. In the bottom panel of Fig. \ref{var-$t$PLF} we display instead different 
